The paper discusses the diffusion of networking technology upgrades in the Internet, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the impact of cascade effects, which is a topic studied in the context of social networks (cs.SOC). The use of linear programming in the algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of optimization and control (cs.SI). The problem of determining the smallest set of nodes that can trigger a cascade is a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the internetwork model, which is a topic studied in the context of information theory (cs.IT).
